layer_change_gcode:
;AFTER_LAYER_CHANGE
;[layer_z]
_MMU_UPDATE_HEIGHT
SET_PRINT_STATS_INFO CURRENT_LAYER={layer_num}          ; For pause at layer functionality and better print stats
LAYER_CHANGE_OFFSET_CHECK LAYER_NUM={layer_num}
machine_start_gcode:
M104 S180      ;  Set the extruder to an initial temperature of 180 just to get the hot end heated
M140 S[bed_temperature_initial_layer_single] 

CG28

SET_PRINT_STATS_INFO TOTAL_LAYER=[total_layer_count]

;MMU_START_SETUP INITIAL_TOOL={initial_tool} TOTAL_TOOLCHANGES=!total_toolchanges! REFERENCED_TOOLS=!referenced_tools! TOOL_COLORS=!colors! TOOL_TEMPS=!temperatures! TOOL_MATERIALS=!materials! FILAMENT_NAMES=!filament_names! PURGE_VOLUMES=!purge_volumes!

;MMU_START_CHECK

QUAD_GANTRY_LEVEL

;-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Custom_Print_Start BED_TEMP=[bed_temperature_initial_layer_single] EXTRUDER_TEMP=[nozzle_temperature_initial_layer] BED_MESH=adaptive   TIMER=30 X_START=5 Y_START=13 X_END=80 Y_END=13 FIRST_LAYER=+0.00 Sensor=True

BEACON_CALIBRATION BED_MESH=adaptive FIRST_LAYER=+0.00 Sensor=True

G90
G1 Z6 F600                       ;   get the head 5mm off the bed as a start position, then the head should restore to this position after the filament load
;------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
;MMU_CALC_PURGE_VOLUMES SOURCE=slicer MULTIPLIER=1.1                 ;   CDW 12/31/2025 - added for the happy hare setup.   getting the purge map from the slicer
;MMU_START_LOAD_INITIAL_TOOL
name: Voron 350 - NO MMU
